1 36-2-108. Appointment of state forester;
2 qualifications; duties.
3
4 (a) The state board of land commissioners shall
5 appoint a state forester who shall be the administrative
6 head of the Wyoming state forestry division of the office
7 of state lands and investments. He shall serve at the
8 pleasure of the board. He shall have a bachelor's degree in
9 forestry with not less than four (4) years experience in
10 professional forestry work. The state forester shall, under
11 the general supervision of the board, have direction of all
12 forest interest and all matters pertaining to forestry
13 within the jurisdiction of the state of Wyoming.; and may,
14 with approval of the board, appoint such assistants and
15 employees as are necessary in executing the duties of his
16 office.
17
18 (b) The state forester shall:
19
20 (viii) Cooperate with federal agencies and all
21 political subdivision of the state to fulfill the intent of
22 this section;.
23
2 SF0152

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0663
1 (ix) Adopt rules as necessary to fulfill the
2 duties described in this article;
3
4 (x) Appoint assistants and employees as are
5 necessary in executing the duties of the division;
6
7 (xi) Maintain wildland and forestry fire control
8 programs including, but not limited to:
9
10 (A) Fire management, coordination and
11 reimbursement for all lands owned and managed by the state
12 of Wyoming and its agencies;
13
14 (B) Fire management assistance within the
15 state of Wyoming;
16
17 (C) Pre-position suppression equipment,
18 personnel and other resources during periods of high
19 wildfire risk;
20
21 (D) Support for local fire jurisdiction
22 training programs;
23
3 SF0152

