1 (E) Establishing standards and regulations
2 for privately contracted private wildland fire resources
3 operating in Wyoming. As used in this subparagraph,
4 "privately contracted private fire resources" includes
5 services retained by insurers for prevention and
6 suppression activities on insured properties.
7
8 Section 2.
9
10 (a) There is created the wildfire management task
11 force to consist of the following members:
12
13 (i) Members of the legislature as follows:
14
15 (A) Two (2) members of the Wyoming house of
16 representatives, appointed by the speaker of the house. The
17 speaker of the house shall designate one (1) of the members
18 appointed under this subparagraph to be co-chairman of the
19 task force;
20
21 (B) Two (2) members of the Wyoming senate,
22 appointed by the president of the senate. The president of
23 the senate shall designate one (1) of the members appointed
4 SF0152

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0663
1 under this subparagraph to be co-chairman of the task
2 force.
3
4 (ii) Members and officials of the Wyoming state
5 government as follows:
6
7 (A) The governor or the governor's
8 designee;
9
10 (B) The president of the Wyoming fire
11 advisory board or the president's designee;
12
13 (C) The Wyoming state forester or the
14 forester's designee;
15
16 (D) The state insurance commissioner or the
17 commissioner's designee.
18
19 (iii) Other members appointed by the governor as
20 follows:
21
22 (A) One (1) member representing Wyoming
23 local governments;
5 SF0152

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0663
1
2 (B) One (1) member representing the
3 agriculture industry;
4
5 (C) One (1) member at large with wildland
6 fire subject matter expertise.
7
8 (b) The task force shall:
9
10 (i) Study the wildfire impacts to private and
11 state lands, state agencies, local fire jurisdictions,
12 individuals and communities;
13
14 (ii) Identify and evaluate wildland fire
15 response systems, including but not limited to, funding,
16 suppression, training, coordination, prevention,
17 mobilization, cooperative agreements and other related
18 programs;
19
20 (iii) Not later than October 1, 2025, report to
21 the governor, the joint agriculture, state and public lands
22 and water resources interim committee and the joint
23 appropriations committee on the work of the task force
6 SF0152

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0663
1 including any recommendations for legislation for
2 consideration by an appropriate legislative committee.
3
4 (c) The task force shall be staffed by the
5 legislative service office.
6
7 (d) The legislative members of the task force shall
8 receive salary, per diem and travel expenses in the manner
9 and amount prescribed by W.S. 28-5-101. Task force members
10 representing Wyoming state government shall be considered
11 to be acting within the scope of regular employment when
12 conducting the official business of the task force and
13 shall receive their regular pay without additional
14 compensation, except that those members shall receive
15 mileage and per diem as provided for other members of the
16 task force under this subsection if the members are not
17 reimbursed by their employer. All other members of the task
18 force shall not receive salary but shall receive per diem
19 and mileage in the amount provided for members of the
20 legislature under W.S. 28-5-101 when conducting the
21 official business of the task force.
22
