1 (iii) Twenty million dollars ($20,000,000.00) to
2 the emergency fire suppression account within the office of
3 state lands and investments.
4
5 (b) There is appropriated from the general fund up to
6 twenty million dollars ($20,000,000.00), or as much thereof
7 as is necessary, to be deposited by the state auditor in
8 the legislative stabilization reserve account for repayment
9 of funds borrowed on or before June 30, 2025 from the
10 legislative stabilization reserve account under 2024
11 Wyoming session laws, chapter 118, section 301(b).
12
13 (c) Funds appropriated in this section shall not be
14 transferred or expended for any other purpose.
15 Notwithstanding W.S. 9-2-1008, 9-2-1012(e) and 9-4-207,
16 funds appropriated in this section shall not lapse at the
17 end of any fiscal period. Any unexpended, unobligated funds
18 at the end of any fiscal period shall remain in the account
19 to which the funds were appropriated and be expended for
20 the purposes specified by this section, except as otherwise
21 provided by further legislative authorization.
22
