1 Section 4. For the period beginning July 1, 2025 and
2 ending June 30, 2026, the governor is authorized to borrow
3 from the legislative stabilization reserve account up to
4 thirty million dollars ($30,000,000.00) as necessary to
5 meet funding requirements to fight wildfires in the event
6 the reserves in the office of state lands and investments'
7 forestry division have been exhausted. The governor shall
8 report to the joint appropriations committee, the president
9 of the senate and the speaker of the house of
10 representatives immediately upon exercise of this
11 authority.
12
13 Section 5. 2024 Wyoming session laws, chapter 118,
14 section 301(b) is repealed.
15
